History.Tyranny of Dragons:
[[File:ToD Adventurers.png|thumb|right|300px|Talon and her allies standing over [[Wyrmspeaker]] [[Varramzord]].]]
In the 1480s DR,{{ToD-time}} Talon joined up with several other adventurers, [[Nymmestra Durothil|Nymmestra]], [[Alaeros Margaster|Alaeros]], [[Barrowin Undurr|Barrowin]], and [[Ratshadow]], an a mission to stop the Cult of the Dragon from retrieving an artifact known as the ''[[Red Dragon Mask]]''.{{Cite web/Tyranny of Dragons: Online Comic 3}}

While out on the isle in the [[Trackless Sea]], Talon and her companions delved into the [[Flame Fault]] and were forced to battle, and eventually slayed [[Lostmauth]],{{ToD-Lost}} one of the three [[red dragon]] rulers of the barbarian isle.{{Cite web/Tyranny of Dragons: Online Comic 4}} Unfortunately, the ''portal'' they used was destroyed and the heroes remained stuck on Tuern for a brief while, allowing the cult's leader [[Severin Silrajin]] to escape with the ''Red Dragon Mask''.{{Cite web/Tyranny of Dragons: Online Comic 5}} 

Moving against the cult again in [[Neverwinter]], the [[Zhentarim]]-aligned Ratshadow went behind the group's back{{Cite web/Tyranny of Dragons: Online Comic 6}} and stashed away the ''[[White Dragon Mask]]'' sought by the cult in [[Waterdeep]].{{Cite web/Tyranny of Dragons: Online Comic 7}} This dastardly action led to the death of Lord [[Arthagast Ulbrinter]], and caused his widow, Lady [[Remallia Haventree]] to launch a political and military crusade against the Cult, at their lair in the [[Well of Dragons]]. Talon and her true-hearted companions were among the heroes that helped apprehend the cult's leader Silrajin and earned praise for their patron organizations.{{Cite web/Tyranny of Dragons: Online Comic 9}}{{Cite web/Tyranny of Dragons: Online Comic 10}}
